---
description: Credit Card Fraud Detection ML Project Rules
globs: ["**/*.py"]
---
- Every .py file must start with a module-level docstring describing its purpose
- Use type hints on every function signature
- Every logical section of code must be separated by a # %% cell marker so the file runs cell-by-cell in VS Code Python Interactive and can be exported to Jupyter notebook
- All functions must have Google-style docstrings with Args and Returns sections
- Use loguru logger for all status messages, never use print()
- Follow PEP8 with max line length 100
- All ML experiments must be reproducible: always use RANDOM_STATE = 42
- Never hardcode file paths — always use pathlib.Path via config.py
- Every script must be runnable standalone with if __name__ == "__main__"
